HEADWORD: Necrophagan
<hw>Ne*croph"a*gan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Necrophagous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Eating
carrion.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any
species of a tribe (<fam>Necrophaga</fam>) of beetles which, in the
larval state, feed on carrion; a burying beetle.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

